[5] Kenya - response to disease forecasts
Date: Mon 15 Jan 2007
From: Peter Roeder <Peter.Roeder@fao.org>

re: Rift Valley fever - Eastern Africa: Somalia, Kenya
-----------------------------------------------
In my message [see 20070112.0164], I lamented the lack of national and
international preparedness for the RVF emergency.
That is still the case, but to be fair, I must mention the fact that the
coordinated actions taken by the veterinary and medical authorities of the
Kenyan Ministries of Health and Livestock and Fisheries Development are
impressive and might well have served to reduce the incidence of human
cases. With very limited funding available and an inadequate resource base,
it is laudable that they have managed to put a coherent response in place.
It seems that at least some lessons were learned from the last RVF pandemic.
--
Dr Peter Roeder, BVetMed, MSc, PhD, MRCVS
Animal Health Officer (Virology) and GREP Secretary
Animal Health Service
Animal Production and Health Division
Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations
Rome, Italy
<peter.roeder@fao.org>
